 <!-- Introduction -->
 <!-- The introduction should start as shown: -->
 <purpose>
   <p>
     This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the
     representation of probability. The module is concerned to record statements about a particular probability, whether expressed numerically, or by some evaluative category, such as "high". The latter is particularly required to support some risk assessment methods.</p> 
	<p>A numerical probability can have its derivation associated by reference to the appropriate probability distribution or statistical modules. In the case of probability distributions, the parameters used to derive the probability can also be recorded.
	The module also records who originated the probability value, and whether it is an estimate or based on some other knowledge or experience.
   </p>
 </purpose>

